  "body": "### Background\r\n`AccessControl.roleData` has a field called `adminRole`.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/ee149877212acf5564921244b3cdaa7266a372fe/contracts/access/AccessControl.sol#L50-L53\r\n\r\nBy default, this will be set to `0x00`. This means that anyone with that role will be an admin (be able to add and remove members) for all roles that don't have a set admin.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, assume a role has set an admin. If this admin role (call it `AR`) has not set its own admin role, the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE would be able to make themselves a member of this role, and hence a member of the administered role.\r\n\r\nIt follows that that the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE can become an admin for every single role, so it is not just default.\r\n\r\nThis recursion works on itself as well - even if the admin **of** the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE is changed, any member of the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE may recusively become an admin of the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE, and hence add or remove other people.\r\n\r\n### Recommendation\r\nRemove this intricate construct by adding checks that `adminRole != \"\"`. This will ensure no default admin exists, greatly simplifying the contract's logic",
