    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hello @hacker-DOM \r\nWhat you are seeing as a bug is in fact a well-thought-out feature.\r\n\r\nBy default, any role that is doesn't have an admin set is administered by the `DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE`. That is what its all about, the `DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE` is plain and simply the default admin role.\r\n\r\nNow, for some reason you want roles A, B and C to manage one another, and not be administered by the default, you can do\r\n\r\n```\r\n_setRoleAdmin(A, A);\r\n_setRoleAdmin(B, A);\r\n_setRoleAdmin(C, B);\r\n```",
